import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['age'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    ax.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    labels = gender_counts.index.tolist()
    sizes = gender_counts.values.tolist()
    fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax1.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax1.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['race'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the racial distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Race')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['death_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['death_date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], s=10, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the geographic distribution of the deaths?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
